---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Substance Use Disorder (SUD) Program">
  <div class="container" style="padding: var(--spacing-6) 0;">
    <nav aria-label="Breadcrumbs" style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-4);">
      <a href="/">Home</a> &gt; <a href="/programs/">Programs</a> &gt; <span aria-current="page">SUD Program</span>
    </nav>
    
    <header style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-6);">
      <h1 style="font-size: 2.5rem; color: var(--color-primary-blue);">Substance Use Disorder (SUD) Support</h1>
      <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--color-text-muted);">Compassionate, structured support for individuals seeking lasting recovery from addiction.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="grid" style="grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr; gap: var(--spacing-6);">
      <div class="main-content">
        <section style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-5);">
          <h2>What the Service Is</h2>
          <p>The Substance Use Disorder (SUD) program at The WEL Foundation provides comprehensive assistance to individuals battling addiction. Through behavioral therapies, mental health coordination, and community support, we offer a dedicated environment designed to empower clients to build and sustain a sober lifestyle. We do not just focus on the symptoms of addiction; we address the whole individual from the inside out.</p>
        </section>

        <section style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-5);">
          <h2>Who It Is For</h2>
          <p>This program is designed for adolescents and adults in the Baltimore community who are actively struggling with a substance use disorder. Whether you are seeking help for the first time or looking for ongoing community support after initial recovery, The WEL Foundation is here to mentor and guide you.</p>
        </section>

        <section style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-5);">
          <h2>How to Qualify</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Must be actively participating in or willing to begin concurrent mental health treatment.</li>
            <li>Must have a referral from a mental health provider or healthcare partner (or initiate a self-referral through our intake process).</li>
            <li>Participation in Maryland Medical Assistance or appropriate pre-arranged coverage is highly recommended.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-5);">
          <h2>What Happens Next</h2>
          <p>Once an intake or referral is submitted, our team reviews the application within <strong>3 business days</strong>. An assigned coordinator will reach out to schedule an initial consultation and evaluation. From there, we work with you to develop a personalized recovery and development plan tailored to your specific needs.</p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <aside>
        <div class="card" style="background-color: var(--color-bg-offset); border-top: 4px solid var(--color-accent-gold);">
          <h3>Take the First Step</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-4);">Our secure intake process is confidential and easy to complete online.</p>
          <a href="/intake/start/" class="btn" style="display: block; width: 100%; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-2);">Start Your Intake</a>
          <a href="/referral/start/" class="btn btn-secondary" style="display: block; width: 100%;">Providers: Refer a Client</a>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
